requestBody.description:
## Warning

Request body must be encrypted.

The request body data would be encrypted as "AES-128(256) / CBC mode / PKCS#5 Padding / Base64 Encoding", through the [EncryptedBody](https://github.com/samchon/@nestia/core#encryptedbody) component.

Therefore, just utilize this swagger editor only for referencing. If you need to call the real API, using [SDK](https://github.com/samchon/nestia#software-development-kit) would be much better.

get.description:
- When namespaced DTO type comes, `@nestia/sdk` had taken a mistake that writing only the deepest type even in the top or middle level namespaced types.
- When propagation mode being used with `@TypedException<T>()` decorator, target `T` type had not been cloned.
- When `clone` mode being used in SDK generator, it was not possible to clone recursive DTO type.
- check optional query DTO
- when use HttpCode decorator, sdk build fail code

openapi.description:
The version of the OpenAPI document.

Nestia always generate OpenAPI 3.0.x document.

servers.description: List of servers that provide the API.

paths.description:
The available paths and operations for the API.

The 1st key is the path, and the 2nd key is the HTTP method.

components.description:
An object to hold reusable data structures.

It stores both DTO schemas and security schemes.

For reference, `nestia` defines every object and alias types as reusable DTO
schemas. The alias type means that defined by `type` keyword in TypeScript.

ISwagger.description:
Swagger Document.

`ISwagger` is a data structure representing content of `swagger.json` file
generated by Nestia. Note that, this is not an universal structure, but a dedicated
structure only for Nestia.

url.description: A URL to the target host.

description.description: An optional string describing the target server.
A short description of the API.

termsOfService.description: A URL to the Terms of Service for the API.

contact.description: The contact information for the exposed API.

license.description: The license information for the exposed API.

name.description: The identifying name of the contact person/organization.

url.description: The URL pointing to the contact information.

email.description: The email address of the contact person/organization.

ISwaggerInfo.IContact.description: Contact information for the exposed API.

name.description: The license name used for the API.

url.description: A URL to the license used for the API.

ISwaggerInfo.ILicense.description: License information for the exposed API.

schemas.description:
An object to hold reusable DTO schemas.

For reference, `nestia` stores every object and alias types as reusable DTO
schemas. The alias type means that defined by `type` keyword in TypeScript.

securitySchemes.description:
An object to hold reusable security schemes.

This property be configured by user in `nestia.config.ts` file.

ISwaggerComponents.description:
Reusable components in Swagger.

`ISwaggerComponents` is a data structure representing content of `components` object
in `swagger.json` file generated by Nestia. Note that, this is not an universal
structure, but a dedicated structure only for Nestia.

Security scheme of Swagger Documents.

`ISwaggerSecurityScheme` is a data structure representing content of

schemes as an union type like below.
